==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coridine
<hw>Co"ri*dine</hw> <pr>(k?"r?-d?n; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
L. <ets>cortium</ets> leather.]</ety> <def>A colorless or yellowish oil,
<chform>C10H15N</chform>, of a leathery odor, occurring in coal tar,
Dippel's oil, tobacco smoke, etc., regarded as an organic base,
homologous with pyridine. Also, one of a series of metameric compounds
of which coridine is a type.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>corindine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corindon</ent>⟦br⟧
